{#-
  New York CFDL / 23 NYCRR § 600.6 — Sales-Based Financing Disclosure.

  Source-of-truth dossier: docs/compliance/02_new_york.md, section
  "What 23 NYCRR § 600.6 requires for MCA disclosures."

  Differs from CA in three ways:
    1. Adds Row 10 — Collateral Requirements
    2. Row 1 includes the NY-specific double-dipping disclosure paragraph
       under § 600.6(b)(3)(v) when the financing is a renewal that pays
       down a prior position with the same provider
    3. Footer cites NY § 600.0 instead of CA § 901

  Variables ({{ }}) are runtime substitutions only — every literal
  regulatory string is from the dossier verbatim. Conditional blocks
  emit additional regulator-prescribed sentences only when the regulation
  says they apply.

  Required context variables (additions vs CA marked +):
    financer_name              str
    funding_provided           str
    recipient_funds            str
    recipient_funds_lt_funding bool
    pays_third_party_payoffs   bool
    third_party_payoff_note    str
   +is_renewal_with_double_dip bool   — true when payoff comes from same provider
   +double_dipping_amount      str    — "$X,XXX.XX" or "$0.00"; only consulted if above is true
    apr                        str
    payment_channel            str
    avg_monthly_income         str
    finance_is_fee_based       bool
    finance_charge             str
    finance_charge_can_increase bool
    estimated_total_payment    str
    estimated_payment_amount   str
    estimated_payment_freq     str
    irregular_payments_note    str
    payment_terms_text         str
    estimated_term             str
    estimated_term_explanation str
    has_monthly_cost_insert    bool
    estimated_monthly_cost     str
    monthly_cost_derivation    str
    prepayment_finance_charge_text str
    prepayment_additional_fee_text str
   +collateral_requirements_text   str  — description, or "None" if no collateral
    rendered_at                str
-#}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Commercial Financing Disclosure — New York (CFDL)</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: -apple-system, sans-serif; max-width: 760px; margin: 24px auto;
         color: #111; }
  h1   { font-size: 18px; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 12px 0; }
  th, td { border: 1px solid #555; padding: 8px 10px; vertical-align: top;
           font-size: 12px; }
  th    { background: #f0f0f0; text-align: left; }
  .col1 { width: 22%; font-weight: 600; }
  .col2 { width: 22%; }
  .col3 { width: 56%; }
  .footer { margin-top: 16px; font-size: 11px; color: #333; }
  .meta   { font-size: 10px; color: #666; margin-top: 6px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Commercial Financing Disclosure</h1>
<p class="meta">New York — 23 NYCRR § 600.6. Provider: {{ financer_name }}.</p>

<table>
<thead>
<tr><th class="col1">&nbsp;</th><th class="col2">&nbsp;</th><th class="col3">&nbsp;</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>

{#- Row 1 — Funding Provided.
    NY-specific addition: when this financing is a renewal that pays
    down a prior position with the same provider, § 600.6(b)(3)(v)
    requires the double-dipping paragraph in a SECOND paragraph
    of column 3. -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Funding Provided</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ funding_provided }}</td>
  <td class="col3">
    <p>This is how much funding {{ financer_name }} will provide.
    {%- if recipient_funds_lt_funding %}
    Due to deductions or payments to others, the total funds that will be
    provided to you directly is {{ recipient_funds }}. For more information
    on what amounts will be deducted, please review the attached document
    "Itemization of Amount Financed."
    {%- endif %}
    {%- if pays_third_party_payoffs %}
    {{ third_party_payoff_note }}
    {%- endif %}
    </p>
    {%- if is_renewal_with_double_dip %}
    <p>Does the renewal financing include any amount that is used to pay
    unpaid finance charges or fees, also known as double dipping?
    {{ double_dipping_amount }}. If the amount is zero, the answer would be No.</p>
    {%- endif %}
  </td>
</tr>

{#- Row 2 — Estimated APR. NY § 600.6 form, with finance-charge wording
    ("finance charges you pay" rather than CA's "fees you pay"). -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Estimated Annual Percentage Rate (APR)</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ apr }}</td>
  <td class="col3">
    APR is the estimated cost of your financing expressed as a yearly rate.
    APR incorporates the amount and timing of the funding you receive,
    finance charges you pay, and the periodic payments you make. This
    calculation assumes your estimated average monthly income through
    {{ payment_channel }} will be {{ avg_monthly_income }}. Since your
    actual income may vary from our estimate, your effective APR may
    also vary.
    {%- if finance_is_fee_based %}
    APR is not an interest rate. The cost of this financing is based upon
    fees charged by {{ financer_name }} rather than interest that accrues
    over time.
    {%- endif %}
  </td>
</tr>

{#- Row 3 — Finance Charge -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Finance Charge</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ finance_charge }}</td>
  <td class="col3">
    This is the dollar cost of your financing.
    {%- if not finance_charge_can_increase %}
    Your finance charge will not increase if you take longer to pay off
    what you owe.
    {%- endif %}
  </td>
</tr>

{#- Row 4 — Estimated Total Payment Amount -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Estimated Total Payment Amount</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ estimated_total_payment }}</td>
  <td class="col3">
    This is the total dollar amount of payments we estimate you will make
    under the contract.
  </td>
</tr>

{#- Optional inserted row — Estimated Monthly Cost (for non-monthly periodic
    payments, i.e. all MCAs). Per § 600.6 inserted BELOW Row 4. -#}
{%- if has_monthly_cost_insert %}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Estimated Monthly Cost</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ estimated_monthly_cost }}</td>
  <td class="col3">{{ monthly_cost_derivation }}</td>
</tr>
{%- endif %}

{#- Row 5 — Estimated Payment.
    Per § 600.6 cols 2+3 are combined: average periodic payment per
    § 600.7 followed by "/" and frequency, plus dates+amounts of
    irregular payments. -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Estimated Payment</td>
  <td class="col2" colspan="2">
    {{ estimated_payment_amount }} / {{ estimated_payment_freq }}
    {%- if irregular_payments_note %}
    <br>{{ irregular_payments_note }}
    {%- endif %}
  </td>
</tr>

{#- Row 6 — Payment Terms (combined cols 2+3 per regulation). -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Payment Terms</td>
  <td class="col2" colspan="2">{{ payment_terms_text }}</td>
</tr>

{#- Row 7 — Estimated Term -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Estimated Term</td>
  <td class="col2">{{ estimated_term }}</td>
  <td class="col3">{{ estimated_term_explanation }}</td>
</tr>

{#- Rows 8 & 9 — Prepayment (col 1 combined as "Prepayment", cols 2+3 combined). -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1" rowspan="2">Prepayment</td>
  <td class="col2" colspan="2">{{ prepayment_finance_charge_text }}</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td class="col2" colspan="2">{{ prepayment_additional_fee_text }}</td>
</tr>

{#- Row 10 — Collateral Requirements (NY-specific; the additional row
    that distinguishes NY's 10-row disclosure from CA's 9-row disclosure). -#}
<tr>
  <td class="col1">Collateral Requirements</td>
  <td class="col2" colspan="2">{{ collateral_requirements_text }}</td>
</tr>

</tbody>
</table>

<p class="footer">New York Applicable law requires this information to be provided to you to help you make an informed decision.</p>

<p class="meta">Generated by AEGIS on {{ rendered_at }}. Per 23 NYCRR § 600.0.</p>
</body>
</html>
